6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Elai and Opus Clip share a solid foundation of core features including Auto Captions, Templates. Where Elai pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Text To Video and Avatar Talking Head and Stock Footage and Voice Over and Api Access, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Opus Clip uniquely offers Batch Processing, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Elai holds an overall score of 6/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Opus Clip scores 8/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Opus Clip comes in at a lower starting price of $15/mo, while Elai begins at $23/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Elai's free tier and Opus Clip's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
